[@SoapDog (SurfaceGo)](@qv10rF4IsmxRZb7g5ekJ33EakYBpdrmV/vtP1ij5BS4=.ed25519) look inside `ssb-tangle`, it has code you can use still on the client side (as many servers offer `ssb-backlinks`)

I would recommend doing 

```js
if (sbot.tangle)  { 
  // use tangle
} else {
  // use sbot.backlinks with the code in there
  // this will take 1 seconds to call from the client side but you can make a cute spinner
}
```

[@Christian Bundy](@+oaWWDs8g73EZFUMfW37R/ULtFEjwKN/DczvdYihjbU=.ed25519) It's doing well, there isn't much mystery around it, there are some remark-supporting React components, e.g. [React-Markdown](https://github.com/rexxars/react-markdown)

```js
const React = require('react')
const ReactDOM = require('react-dom')
const ReactMarkdown = require('react-markdown')
const gemojiToEmoji = require('remark-gemoji-to-emoji');
const stripHtml = require('remark-strip-html');
const imagesToSsbServeBlobs = require('remark-images-to-ssb-serve-blobs');
const ref = require('ssb-ref')
const linkifyRegex = require('remark-linkify-regex');
const linkifySsbFeeds = linkifyRegex(ref.feedIdRegex);
const linkifySsbMsgs = linkifyRegex(ref.msgIdRegex);

const input = '# This is a header\n\nAnd this is a paragraph' // Or scuttlebutt content

const source = source: remark()
      .use(gemojiToEmoji)
      .use(stripHtml)
      .use(linkifySsbFeeds)
      .use(linkifySsbMsgs)
      .use(imagesToSsbServeBlobs)
      .processSync(input).contents;

ReactDOM.render(
  <ReactMarkdown source={source} />,
  document.getElementById('container')
)
```

@mix: That came of wrong/to entangled, I guess. I found it slow when patchcore started but don't find it _as slow_ anymore. Definetly gotten much better. It doesn't take as long to load and display the names. Back then when I stopped using it I feared it would end in an _eternal rewrite_ cycle which I felt bad about since I lack the js design insights to help at that level. patchcore/depject is still dark wizardry for me and I couldn't follow half of the design discussions back then but from the two PRs today I definetly find stuff to contribute so I think you guise definetly pulled through that savanna of cypherspace.

